Description . Habitus typical of the genus. Body length (without antennae): holotype 0.84 mm, paratype (first instar) 0.77 mm. Colour of the body white. 2 + 2 medium dark-pigmented eyes (
Fig. 1
).

Types of dorsal ordinary chaetae. Macrochaetae Ml relatively long, strongly thickened, almost cylindrical, arclike or straight, narrowly sheathed, feebly serrated, apically rounded or rarely pointed (mostly in lateral part of body) (
Figs 1, 5 , 8–10
); macrochaetae Mc and Mcc thickened, straight and blunt; mesochaetae and microchaetae short, thin, feebly serrated and pointed.
